<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sergio Ramos scored an 82nd minute penalty to give Real Madrid all three points at Real Betis on Saturday night.</p>

<p>Zinedine Zidane's side had to come back from 2-1 down but did so thanks to Emerson's own goal and Ramos' penalty. Emerson also saw red midway through the second half.</p>

<p>Fede Valverde gave Madrid the lead before goals from Aissa Mandi and William Carvalho had the hosts in front in Seville.</p>

<p>But after Emerson put the ball into his own net, Ramos stepped up to convert from 12 yards to earn the reigning LaLiga champions their first win of the season.</p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Sergio Ramos scored an 82nd minute penalty to give Real Madrid all three points at Real Betis</p>

<p>Ramos showed his composure by doing his trademark chipped penalty to seal the three points</p>

<p>Betis goalkeeper Joel Robles committed to his right but Ramos dinked down the middle</p>

<p>Uruguayan midfielder Fede Valverde fires into the back of the net to give Real the lead</p>

<p>Valverde is mobbed by his team-mates after scoring the opening goal of the match</p>

<p>But they were not ahead for long with defender Aissa Mandi bringing Betis level with a header</p>

<p>Mandi celebrates with his team-mates after netting at the Benito Villamarin stadium in Seville</p>

<p>Real Betis: Robles, Emerson, Mandi, Bartra, Moreno, Rodriguez, Carvalho, Joaquin (Tello 63), Fekir (Loren 73), Canales, Sanabria (Montoya 69). </p>

